match_description: Small startup needs its first designer/marketer/etc.; candidate wants exactly that role.

profiles.raw_input: Hi there! I'm Alex Rivera, founder of PixelPerfect. We're a brand new design-focused SaaS startup that just secured initial funding. We've built our MVP and now need our first talented marketing designer to help us establish our brand identity and create compelling visual content for our launch. I have a technical background but need someone creative who's excited about joining a tiny team and wearing multiple hats. Looking for that special someone who wants to be employee #1 and grow with us!

personal.name: Alex Rivera
personal.headline: Founder of PixelPerfect - Early-stage SaaS startup hiring our first designer

roles.title: Founder & CEO
highlights: Previous experience as lead developer at enterprise SaaS company

profiles.extra_notes: Our product helps marketing teams streamline their creative workflow. Looking specifically for our first design hire who's excited about building a brand from scratch. Competitive salary and equity package available.

profiles.raw_input: Hello! I'm Jamie Nguyen, a UX/UI designer with 4 years of experience at established companies. I'm specifically looking to join an early-stage startup as their first design hire where I can make a real impact and establish the visual foundation for a growing company. I have experience in brand identity, marketing collateral, and product design. I'm particularly drawn to opportunities where I can wear multiple hats and grow alongside the company rather than being siloed into a narrow role at a large organization.

personal.name: Jamie Nguyen
personal.headline: Designer seeking to be first design hire at an early-stage startup

roles.title: Senior UI/UX Designer
highlights: Created brand identity for 2 major product lines
Led design for marketing campaigns that increased user acquisition by 45%
Mentored junior designers on the team

profiles.extra_notes: I'm specifically interested in being the first design hire at a startup where I can establish the visual language and brand identity from the ground up. Looking for a company with a clear product vision but needing someone to translate that into compelling visual experiences.
